NACALPowerFS Cc PST Hey Cooper I would like to get your opinion and approval on a couple of things Wed like to get a development IIS server running and so would also like to move your development from NETCos only production IIS server to this new server I believe Greg is setting this up shortly Since the PowerFS server is now the production web server for all of NETCo wed like to move the IIS administration duties to the IT team which would most likely mean to me Im assuming you have these duties right now If not maybe you could point me in the right direction Also because of that we need to move at least one web application on to PowerFSPresenter is the one NETCo web app moving over that is in Production Origman will be there shortly as well Since Pavel used MSXML with SP and would need it on the box I was wondering what version are you running He tells me that multiple versions can be run at the same time as they are separately named libraries and files Thanks for your time Let me know what you think about all of this Chris Wiebe Staff Data Technologies Enron Canada Corp Phone Cell Email Chris nroncom

RE development stored procs to prodPST Just an FYI if you want to alter procedures in production already you can use the command Alter Procedure instead of Create Procedure Everything else would be as you have it in your scripts All it does is change the code of the procedure without touching dependencies or permissions Ill change that in these so that you dont have to Thanks Chris Wiebe Staff Data Technologies Enron Canada Corp Phone Cell Pager Pager email Email Chris nroncom Original Message From Richey Cooper Sent Thursday October PM To Wiebe Chris Subject development stored procs to prod can you update the following procs in prod with these scripts while maintain existing set of permissions File sppoolpricesql File spsql File spsql thx cooper
